data.name: 107 Taste
data.description: 107 Taste was established by Chef Yu and her husband Dr. Lei. Opening a restaurant has always been Chef Yu’s childhood dream. Chef Yu was raised by her grandparents in a small village in northwestern China. Her grandmother worked as a Chef for more than 20 years, and her grandfather’s family used to own a local famous wonton restaurant in Szechuan, China back in the 1930s. Her entire childhood memories are full of grandparents’ care, and she grew up with unbeatable grandmother’s love meal. After married with Dr. Lei, the couple decided to work hard together and make Yu’s dream come true, so they started to open the first 107 Taste on February, 2016, in Westchester, FL on 107the Ave (this is how the name “107 Taste” comes from!), right across FIU main campus. Since then, the couple had been working even harder because they want to bring gourmet food to more people in south FL!

data.name: Dr. Limon Ceviche Bar - FIU
data.description: When it comes to authentic Peruvian food, most people think of Ceviche. We thought of just that and didn't stop there. We wanted to make it a fun and enjoyable culinary experience for everyone and decided to launch a fresh new restaurant concept, named after our chef and owner Carlos Brescia's nickname, Dr. Limon. Our approach is Peruvian food with a Miami twist, influenced by traditional northern Peruvian cuisine and respecting local South Florida businesses and ingredients. Located near Florida International University in the Florida International Plaza.
